excerpt: Originally built in 1751, this 200-m. stone pier is named after the Italian Navy destroyer Audace.
detail_description: Molo Audace, a historic stone pier established in 1751, is steeped in rich maritime history and cultural significance. Originally named San Carlo pier after a shipwreck, it gained its current name following a poignant event on November 3, 1918, when the destroyer Audace docked here to mark Trieste's annexation to Italy. This moment was celebrated by an ecstatic crowd that welcomed General Pelitti Roreto as he proclaimed the city's new allegiance.
name: Molo Audace
address: 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Hilltop 14th-century cathedral built on a Roman temple, known for its elaborate frescoes & mosaics.
detail_description: Perched atop a hill, the Cattedrale di San Giusto Martire is a stunning 14th-century cathedral that beautifully marries history and artistry. Built on the remnants of a Roman temple, this architectural gem showcases intricate frescoes and mesmerizing mosaics that reflect both Byzantine and modern influences. As you wander through Trieste, this cathedral stands out among other remarkable sites like the Serbian Orthodox Church of San Spiridone and the grand Synagogue.
name: Cattedrale di San Giusto Martire
address: P.za della Cattedrale, 2, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Imposing 15th-century castle & fort, now housing a museum of historical weapons & local history.
detail_description: The Castello di San Giusto is a striking 15th-century castle and fortress that now serves as a museum showcasing historical weapons and local history. This impressive structure also hosts various events, including a festival featuring historical and contemporary music groups.
name: Castello di San Giusto
address: P.za della Cattedrale, 3, 34131 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Perched on the hill of Trieste, the Castle of Saint Giusto has a rich history dating back to Roman times. Originally a Roman fort, it was reconstructed by Friedrich II of Habsburg in 1470 and now houses the museum of Trieste. The castle offers stunning views of the sea and city. Visitors can explore medieval weapons at the museum and admire Roman sculptures and inscriptions at the Tergestino Lapidary.
name: Castle of Saint Giusto
address: Via della Cattedrale, 3, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Compact Roman amphitheater dating to roughly the 1st century CE, with occasional performances.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Trieste, the Roman Theatre of Trieste is a captivating glimpse into ancient history, dating back to the 1st century CE. This well-preserved amphitheater, located on Via del Teatro Romano near Piazza Unità d'Italia, showcases remarkable Roman architecture with its seating arrangements and stage area still intact.
name: Roman Theatre of Trieste
address: Via del Teatro Romano, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Museum for the fine & decorative arts collection of a 19th-century baron in his elegant former home.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Trieste, the Revoltella Museum is a captivating destination for art enthusiasts and history buffs alike. Housed in the elegant former residence of Baron Pasquale Revoltella, a 19th-century merchant with a flair for modernity, this museum showcases an impressive collection that spans from the early 19th century to contemporary works.
name: Revoltella Museum
address: Via Armando Diaz, 27, 34123 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Elegant 1700s church & spiritual home for the Serbian Orthodox community of Trieste.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Trieste, the Serbian Orthodox Church of Saint Spyridon stands as a testament to the city's rich cultural tapestry. Constructed in 1748, this elegant church serves as a spiritual haven for the local Serbian Orthodox community and showcases stunning architecture that contrasts beautifully with its Roman Catholic counterparts. The church's historical significance is underscored by its establishment prior to the official recognition of Orthodox practices in Trieste, which only came about three years later.
name: Serbian Orthodox Church of Saint Spyridon
address: Via S. Spiridione, 9, 34122 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Trieste is the capital city of the Friuli Venezia Giulia region in northeast Italy. A port city, it occupies a thin strip of land between the Adriatic coast and Slovenia’s border on the limestone-dominated Karst Plateau. Italian, Austro-Hungarian and Slovenian influences are all evident in its layout, which encompasses a medieval old city and a neoclassical Austrian quarter.
detail_description: Trieste, the capital city of the Friuli Venezia Giulia region in northeast Italy, is a charming port city with a blend of Italian, Austro-Hungarian, and Slovenian influences. The city's layout encompasses a medieval old town and a neoclassical Austrian quarter.
name: Trieste
address: Province of Trieste, Italy

excerpt: Lighthouse commemorating World War I sailors, sometimes open to the public for panoramic bay views.
detail_description: Perched majestically above the Gulf of Trieste, the Victory Lighthouse, or Faro della Vittoria, stands as a striking tribute to both maritime navigation and the valor of World War I sailors. Towering at an impressive 223 feet, it ranks among the tallest lighthouses globally.
name: Victory Lighthouse
address: Str. del Friuli, 141, 34136 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Ornate 19th-century place of worship featuring a gold apse, a large rose window & marble columns.
detail_description: The Trieste Synagogue is a grand 19th-century place of worship adorned with a gold apse, marble columns, and a large rose window. It stands out among the city's architectural wonders alongside the San Giusto cathedral and Miramare castle. The synagogue is part of Trieste's diverse cultural landscape, which includes magnificent churches representing various religions.
name: Trieste Synagogue
address: Via S. Francesco D'Assisi, 19, 34133 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Piazza Unità d'Italia, also known as the Unity of Italy Square, is a grand and expansive square located in Trieste. It is one of the largest squares in Europe and is surrounded by magnificent palatial buildings on three sides, while the fourth side opens out to the Adriatic Sea. Despite its name celebrating Italy's foundation, it only became part of Italy after World War I.
name: Piazza Unità d'Italia
address: 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Piazza della Borsa is situated in the modern part of the city, known as Borgo Teresiano, which showcases neoclassical city planning from the 18th century. This area was expanded when Trieste was declared a Free Port of the Austrian Empire. The square is located near Piazza Unita Italia and offers a glimpse into local life and an opportunity to savor delicious meals.
name: Piazza della Borsa
address: 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Set in a notable square with bars & eateries, this ancient arch is said to have been built in 33 BC.
detail_description: Located in a bustling square with various dining options, Arco di Riccardo is an ancient arch believed to have been constructed in 33 BC. It is one of the oldest architectural remnants in Trieste and holds historical significance. Legend has it that the arch was named after King Richard of England, who was rumored to have been imprisoned there during his return from the Crusades. The site is tucked away in a charming alley and offers visitors a chance to connect with history.
name: Arco di Riccardo
address: Piazza del Barbacan, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt:
Muggia is an Italian comune in the regional decentralization entity of Trieste, in the region of Friuli-Venezia Giulia on the border with Slovenia. It has 12,703 inhabitants.
Lying on the eastern flank of the Gulf of Trieste in the northern Adriatic Sea, Muggia is the only Italian port town in Istria. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Muggia is a charming Italian town located in the southeastern region of Trieste, within the picturesque Friuli Venezia Giulia. Situated on the border with Slovenia, it boasts a unique position on the eastern side of the Gulf of Trieste in the northern Adriatic Sea. As the only Italian port town in Istria, Muggia offers visitors a glimpse into its small fishing village and rich maritime heritage.
name: Muggia
address: 34015 Province of Trieste, Italy

detail_description: Borgo Teresiano is the modern part of the city, featuring an orderly grid of streets and stylish palaces. This neoclassical area was established in the early 18th century under Emperor Charles VI and Empress Mary Theresa's expansion of the city, declaring it a Free Port.
name: Borgo Teresiano
address: 34132 Trieste, Province of Trieste, Italy

excerpt: Established in 1846, this natural history museum features plants, minerals, curiosities & more.
detail_description: Nestled in the charming city of Trieste, the Civic Museum of Natural History has been captivating visitors since its establishment in 1846. This fascinating museum showcases an impressive collection that spans over four million specimens, including remarkable dinosaur skeletons—most notably, the nearly intact Tethyshadros insularis named Antonio. As you wander through its halls, you'll encounter a variety of intriguing exhibits ranging from ancient dental care artifacts to crocodile fossils and even a massive five-meter-long white shark.
name: Civic Museum of Natural History
address: Via dei Tominz, 4, 34139 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Elegant, 19th-century villa museum hung with paintings, plus furniture & drawings collections.
detail_description: The Civico Museo Sartorio, housed in a charming 18th-century villa that once belonged to the Sartorio family, has recently reopened after extensive refurbishment. The museum showcases the original furnishings and decor of the mansion, including porcelain, ceramics, and an impressive art collection. The Rusconi-Opuich collection features around 2500 pieces of various artworks spanning from ancient to contemporary times.
name: Civico Museo Sartorio
address: Largo Papa Giovanni XXIII, 1, 34123 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Historic coffee house known for its literati clientele, serving espresso, pastries & light meals.
detail_description: Caffè San Marco is a historic coffee house in Trieste, Italy, known for its literati clientele and timeless atmosphere. With over a century of history, it offers a magical ambiance in its well-kept dining room, outdoor terrace, and library spaces where events and book presentations take place.
name: Caffè San Marco
address: Via Cesare Battisti, 18, 34125 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Opera & ballet showcased in an 18th-century theater with box seats & ornate, gilded architecture.
detail_description: Teatro Lirico Giuseppe Verdi is an 18th-century theater known for showcasing opera and ballet. The ornate, gilded architecture and box seats add to the charm of this venue. It has a rich history of hosting world premieres of various shows. Additionally, it is part of a vibrant cultural scene that includes other theaters offering prose, dance, musicals, and more.
name: Teatro Lirico Giuseppe Verdi
address: Piazza Giuseppe Verdi, 1, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Pasticceria La Bomboniera is a historical pastry shop that has been enchanting visitors since 1836 with its perfectly preserved Art Nouveau furnishings and vintage wood-fired oven. This fairy-tale place offers a heart-stopping selection of cakes, pastries, and chocolates based on Austro-Hungarian tradition.
name: Pasticceria La Bomboniera
address: Via Trenta Ottobre, 3, 34122 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Former rice factory, used by the Nazis as a concentration camp, now a modern memorial & museum.
detail_description: San Sabba Rice Mill National Monument and Museum, located just outside the heart of Trieste, is a profound historical site that invites visitors to reflect on its somber past. Originally built in 1898 as a rice husking facility, it tragically transformed into the only Nazi concentration camp on Italian soil during World War II. This complex served as a grim location for the detention and extermination of thousands, including political dissidents and Jewish individuals.
name: San Sabba Rice Mill National Monument and Museum
address: Via Giovanni Palatucci, 5, 34148 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Strada Vicentina, also known as the Napoleonic Road, is a picturesque walking and cycling trail that stretches approximately 3.7km (2.3 miles) from Villa Opicina to Borgo San Nazario car park in Prosecco. This easily accessible path offers stunning panoramic views of the Gulf of Trieste and the city. It is a popular route for both locals and visitors, providing beautiful glimpses of nature and connecting Opicina to Prosecco.
name: Strada Vicentina
address: 34151 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Brioches, coffee & hot chocolate at a venerable cafe with an old-world interior & piazza tables.
detail_description: Caffè degli Specchi is a venerable cafe located in Trieste, Italy. Situated facing the Mediterranean Sea, it is surrounded by the city's public offices and an elegant hotel. The interior exudes an old-world charm, offering a perfect setting for enjoying brioches, coffee, and hot chocolate.
name: Caffè degli Specchi
address: Piazza Unità d'Italia, 7, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Imposing neoclassical church, built in the 19th century, with soaring Ionic columns & a domed roof.
detail_description: Located in the heart of Borgo Teresiano, the Church of Sant'Antonio Nuovo is an impressive neoclassical structure built in the 19th century. The church features soaring Ionic columns and a domed roof, with six statues adorning its facade. Situated near the Grand Canal, it offers picturesque views from Ponte Verde bridge at Riva Tre Novembre street.
name: Church of Sant'Antonio Nuovo
address: Via Amilcare Ponchielli, 2, 34122 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: In the charming city of Trieste, Italy, the James Joyce statue stands as a tribute to the renowned Irish novelist and poet. This beautiful sculpture by Nino Spagnoli was placed on Ponte Rosso bridge in 2004 to commemorate the centenary of Joyce's arrival in Trieste. The city served as an inspiration for Joyce while he worked on his masterpiece, Ulysses.
name: James Joyce statue
address: V. Roma, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Charming museum documenting local theatrical & musical history with posters, instruments & costumes.
detail_description: Palazzo Gopcevich is a charming museum located alongside the Grand Canal in Trieste, Italy. The building itself is a sight to behold, with intricate details that make it worth a closer look. Inside, visitors can explore a collection of local theatrical and musical history through old photographs, posters, instruments, and costumes. The museum showcases the city's rich cultural heritage with exhibits on Italian theatre, opera, and music.
name: Palazzo Gopcevich
address: Via Gioacchino Rossini, 4, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Cocktails, coffee & Viennese-style pastries, plus pizza & pasta, at an elegant, Habsburg-era cafe.
detail_description: Caffè Tommaseo is an elegant and refined café located in Trieste, Italy. It offers a variety of cocktails, coffee, Viennese-style pastries, pizza, and pasta. The café has a rich history dating back to its opening as Caffe Tomaso by owner Tomaso Marcato from Padova. Over time, it became a favorite meeting place for artists and businessmen due to its sophisticated ambiance.
name: Caffè Tommaseo
address: Piazza Nicolò Tommaseo, 4, 34122 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Canal Grande, located in the heart of Trieste, is a historic waterway that served as a vital route for transporting goods to the city's port. Constructed in the 18th century, it remains a significant symbol of Trieste's past and present. The area around Canal Grande features notable landmarks such as Ponte Rosso and the renowned statue of James Joyce.
name: Canal Grande
address: P.za Sant'Antonio Nuovo, 34122 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: The Palazzo del Municipio di Trieste, also known as Il Municipio, is a significant building in the city and currently serves as the city hall. It was designed by local architect Giuseppe Bruni and constructed between 1873 and 1875. The eclectic style of its facade gives it a monumental and grand appearance, dominating the Piazza dell'Unita d'Italia with a stunning view towards the sea.
name: Trieste city hall
address: Piazza Unità d'Italia, 4, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Piazza Unità d'Italia is a must-see in Trieste, known for its grandeur and historical significance. It is one of the largest piazzas in Europe and is surrounded by magnificent palatial buildings that give it a wedding cake-like appearance. Despite being named after Italy's foundation, it only became part of Italy in 1919.
name: Piazza Unità d'Italia
address: 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

name: via dei Tominz (museo di storia naturale)
address: 34139 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: B&B Old Town Rooms is located in the historic center, which includes the former Jewish Ghetto. The area is a labyrinth of narrow streets that lead up to Colle di San Giusto. Visitors can enjoy leisurely strolls and explore artisan workshops, cozy bars, and charming vintage shops. While some may not have personally visited the place, they have heard positive things about it.
name: B&B Old Town Rooms
address: Via dei Fabbri, 3, 34124 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Museum with model ships & artifacts relating to the navy, fishing & regional seafaring history.
detail_description: The Civico Museo del Mare is a captivating museum that showcases an extensive collection of model ships and artifacts related to naval history, fishing, and regional seafaring. The museum's focus lies in the sailing ships of the Adriatic and Tyrrhenian Sea, as well as historical fishing craft. Visitors can explore three floors filled with scale models, period instruments, equipment, drawings, photographs, and nautical charts.
name: Civico Museo del Mare
address: Via di Campo Marzio, 5, 34123 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Historic subterranean complex of WWII Italian & German air-raid shelters, with monthly group tours.
detail_description: Kleines Berlin, nestled beneath the vibrant streets of Trieste, is a fascinating historical site that transports visitors back to the tumultuous times of World War II. This extensive network of underground air-raid shelters served as a refuge for civilians and a strategic headquarters for German troops during their occupation. Spanning several kilometers, this remarkable complex showcases two distinct sections—one constructed by Italians and the other by Germans—each reflecting different architectural styles from that era.
name: Kleines Berlin
address: Via Fabio Severo, 34133 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Indoor market with fruit, vegetable, meat & fish vendors, plus upstairs stalls for clothes & shoes.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Trieste, the Mercato Coperto is a charming indoor market that invites visitors to embark on a delightful shopping journey. This historic gem, built in 1936, boasts an impressive Art Deco exterior and houses a variety of stalls offering fresh fruits and vegetables, regional cheeses, cured meats, and artisanal goods.
name: Mercato Coperto Trieste
address: Via Giosuè Carducci, 36, 34125 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Free-admission museum featuring prints, sculptures, objects & cultural artifacts from China & Japan.
detail_description: Located near the main city square, Piazza dell'Unita d'Italia, the Civic Museum of Oriental Art in Trieste is a testament to the historical ties between the port city and the Orient. The museum offers free admission and showcases an array of prints, sculptures, cultural artifacts, and objects from China and Japan.
name: Civic Museum of Oriental Art
address: Via S. Sebastiano, 1, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Nestled at the base of San Giusto Hill in Trieste, the Parish of Santa Maria Maggiore stands as a testament to the city's rich religious heritage. This Baroque-style church, which began construction in 1627 and was completed by 1682, is deeply intertwined with the Jesuit congregation that arrived in Trieste in 1619. Its impressive architecture draws visitors from near and far, inviting them to ascend its grand steps and explore its serene interior.
name: Parrocchia di Santa Maria Maggiore
address: Via del Collegio, 6, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: The city of Trieste has been a source of inspiration for many renowned artists, including Italo Svevo, Umberto Saba, James Joyce, Rainer Maria Rilke, and Sigmund Freud. The bronze statue of Italo Svevo in Piazza Hortis was created by the local sculptor Nino Spagnoli in 2004.
name: Statue of Italo Svevo
address: Piazza Attilio Hortis, 1, 34123 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Steps to a hilltop lookout amid grass slopes & trees, with memorial stones for the city's war dead.
detail_description: Parco della Rimembranza is a serene and picturesque park located in the heart of Trieste, Italy. It features a hilltop lookout with memorial stones honoring the city's war dead. The lush greenery and peaceful ambiance make it an ideal spot for a family or romantic stroll. The park offers panoramic views of the city from its elevated position, providing visitors with a tranquil setting to relax and enjoy nature.
name: Parco della Rimembranza
address: V.le della Rimembranza, 34131 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Giants' Stairway, also known as Scala dei Giganti, is a grand neoclassical stairway in Trieste that connects the city center with San Giusto Hill. Designed by the Berlams in 1970, it features double stairways, niches with statues, and a large fountain at the top. Visitors recommend experiencing it both during the day and at night when the top fountain is illuminated with Italian flag colors. The climb offers stunning panoramic views of Trieste.
name: Giants' Stairway
address: 34122 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: James Joyce's life & work are celebrated at this dedicated museum with displays & Bloomsday events.
detail_description: Museo Joyce is a dedicated museum in Trieste that celebrates the life and work of James Joyce. It houses original materials and documents from Joyce's time in Trieste, offering visitors the opportunity to deepen their knowledge of the renowned Irish writer. The museum features an up-to-date library with editions of his works and a complete collection of major magazines discussing Joyce in English. Visitors can explore the trail of his favorite spots and learn about his connection to Trieste.
name: Museo Joyce
address: Presso Museo LETS - Letteratura Trieste, Piazza Attilio Hortis, 4, 34124 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Delikatessen Modernariato & Collezionismo, located in Via Felice Venezian, is a flagship antique store in the city. It offers a wide range of vintage items such as furniture, suitcases, lamps, and postcards. In December, the store transforms into an Aladdin's cave with a stunning collection of vintage Christmas baubles. Customers have praised the owners' courtesy and competence in rediscovering the flavor of the past through their unique objects.
name: Delikatessen Modernariato & Collezionismo
address: Via Felice Venezian, 10/C, 34124 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Museo d'Arte Moderna Ugo Carà, located at Via Roma 9 in Muggia, is a charming museum that hosts various temporary exhibitions. The museum's structure is excellent and it contains many interesting things to explore. Visitors are welcomed warmly and can receive detailed information about the museum and its contents upon entry. The museum also features the splendid Bressanutti gallery, making it an ideal space for exhibitions.
name: Museo d'Arte Moderna Ugo Carà
address: Via Roma, 9, 34015 Muggia TS, Italy

detail_description: Colle di San Giusto is a historic site located in the center of the old town, featuring a well-preserved Roman theatre at the bottom of San Giusto hill. The climb to the top offers majestic views and leads to an austere interior with splendid mosaics. Visitors can also explore the bell tower with its famous bells and enjoy panoramic views of the city.
name: Colle di San Giusto
address: 34128 Trieste, Province of Trieste, Italy

excerpt: Longstanding venue with sidewalk tables, known for Trieste-style boiled meat platters & broths.
detail_description: Buffet da Pepi is a well-established venue in Trieste, known for its traditional Trieste-style boiled meat platters and broths. Located at Via della Cassa di Risparmio, it offers a variety of dishes such as marinated eggplants, lasagna with sea bass and zucchini, and stuffed crepes with artichokes. The menu also includes typical hot pot dishes and a selection of sandwiches filled with ham, smoked pork loin, or cotechino sausage.
name: Buffet da Pepi
address: Via della Cassa di Risparmio, 3, 34121 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Trattoria Mara is a family-owned restaurant in Trieste that offers a homely atmosphere and traditional Friulian recipes. The menu features typical dishes from the region, including cjalsons, Friulian frika, potato dumplings with goulash, polenta, pasta, soups, and homemade desserts. The restaurant is known for its informal yet fantastic food served in a friendly and fun environment. It's advisable to make reservations due to its popularity.
name: Trattoria Mara
address: Via Vittoria Colonna, 5, 34124 Trieste TS, Italy

detail_description: Eataly Trieste offers a relaxed and inviting atmosphere with a stunning view of the Sacchetta. Whether it's winter or summer, this place provides a comfortable setting to savor various blends and mixtures from different origins. Partnered with Starhotels, Eataly aims to export the essence of Italy worldwide through its high-quality products.
name: Eataly Trieste
address: Riva Tommaso Gulli, 1, 34123 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Seafood & pasta dishes, plus Central European wines, in an easygoing space with a brick archway.
detail_description: Trattoria Nerodiseppia is a charming trattoria in Trieste, Italy, known for its delicious seafood and pasta dishes paired with Central European wines. The restaurant's easygoing space features a brick archway that adds to its cozy atmosphere. Run by the passionate partners Valentina and Giulio Cusma, the trattoria has gained recognition for its top-quality cuisine, particularly focusing on fresh catches of the day sourced from the Marano lagoon to Istria and Trieste waters.
name: Trattoria Nerodiseppia
address: Via Luigi Cadorna, 23, 34123 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Neapolitan-style pizza, pasta & grilled mains in a relaxed, family-run locale with sidewalk tables.
detail_description: Al Barattolo is a family-run pizza restaurant located close to the Canal Grande in Trieste, Italy. They're known for their Neapolitan-style pizzas as well as pasta and grilled main courses. Their wine list features wines from various Italian regions, making it the perfect place to enjoy a delicious meal with friends.
name: Al Barattolo
address: P.za Sant'Antonio Nuovo, 2/d, 34122 Trieste TS, Italy

excerpt: Casual eatery & bar featuring a rooftop terrace & waterfront dining, plus standard regional cuisine.
detail_description: PIER is a casual eatery and bar located in Trieste, Italy, featuring a rooftop terrace and waterfront dining. The restaurant offers standard regional cuisine, making it a great spot to enjoy delicious and simple dishes. For those looking for vegetarian, vegan, or gluten-free options, Melogranos is recommended for its delicious pizzas and dishes prepared with local ingredients. Additionally, Caffe Sacher is worth mentioning for its special meals and simple sandwiches.
name: Pier The Roof
address: Molo Venezia, 1, 34123 Trieste TS, Italy
